Disappointing Stay
Nov 2023 • Family
We stay at Red Rock every time we go to Las Vegas, which is about 3-4 times a year. We are usually very happy and love staying there. We bring friends and promote the hotel to everyone we talk to, however this time was the worst experience. We checked in and requested a room close to the elevator, we got a room two doors from the opposite end of the elevator. We needed a refrigerator to store some perishable items and had to "rent" one for $15/day+tax. The room had a refrigerator with items for purchase and a sign that stated the refrigerator could not be used for personal items or a fee will be charged $25/day. A refrigerator is a nice convenance and should be available in every room for guest to use. We also asked for comps for meals from the pit bosses and were told that because we are guest staying at the hotel, charge everything to your room and at the end a Casino Host will review your play and determine if you are eligible for any comps. We normally get a few comps, which the Pit Bosses offer us for meals. However this time when we checked with the Casino Host, they told us we had nothing. My husband's play leveled up to the next tier during our stay. We didn't expect everything to be complementary but one meal at least (we only charge two meals). We also were told that we could not get a shuttle to the airport and to get a Lyft, Uber or Taxi. :-( Each situation by itself would have been acceptable but the combination altogether left a bad vibe for the trip.
Written November 16, 2023

Not family friendly
Nov 2023 • Family
We recently stayed at the Red Rock with our young family, children 6,4, and 10 months old. Upon arrival we noticed the snack area and requested it be removed. They said it would be a charge to do so. The most concerning part, was that it was filled with candy at child level, even my baby could reach it, worst of all it was weighted, so if it was removed you only had 15 secs to put it back before you were charged. Talk about stressful. The lovely bell hop suggested putting a towel over it, thankfully thatbseemed tondo the trick. They also do not offer a refrigerator, the one they do provide, is again filled with drinks and candy you are not allowed to use it for personal use and again cost money to remove it. Thankfully, they had a refrigerator available on request, but it was only free due to my husband's need to refrigerate his medicine. We also, had awful neighbours who called noise control on our children and were banging on the walls. It was 12.30 pm and 7.30pm and once more around 8pm(this one was literally the baby squealing, not sure what we are meant to do about a baby making noise) it was over all a very stressful experience for our two days that was meant to be a relaxing time. Obviously, bad neighbours are not the fault of the hotel, but it added to the stressful experience overall. I would say although, the hotel has family attractions it is not set up for families at all.
Written November 11, 2023

Red Rock pool rocks!
Oct 2023 • Couples
We headed out to Red Rock Casino and Resort for our last day in Vegas (late flight back east so we had time to kill). We got a pool day pass and checked our bags with the Bell Desk. Get your day passes the day of versus ordering online (call ahead to get a sense of volume at the pool). On shower days (like when we were there) they will give you a discount or only charge for one adult. The pool is fantastic. Music is not too loud and the bar is good for food and drinks. Lots of food options at this place for dinner. For TBones make sure you have a reservation (we didn’t and missed out!). This was worth the day pass for a peaceful day before heading home.
Written October 7, 2023
